title: Minnesota blasts Boliermakers
text:
Purdue University Boilermakers October 10, 2015 Updated Oct 10, 2015 at 10:34 PM EDT 
(West Lafayette, Indiana) -- Minnesota freshman running back Shannon Brooks rushed for a season - high 176 yards including a game - breaking 71 - yard touchdown run early in the second half that led Minnesota to a 41 - 13 blowout at Purdue. The FBS' second - lowest scoring offense scored 28 in the third quarter alone, more than it had scored in any game of its previous five games, and the Big Ten's worst rushing team piled up a season - best 326 yards on the ground. Purdue's woes continued as the Boilermakers fell to 1 - 5 for the season.
